description:
agon-mos API:
  mos_uopen  (15h): open UART with given baud rate
  mos_uclose (16h): close UART
  mos_ugetc  (17h): read byte from UART (blocking)
  mos_uputc  (18h): write byte to UART

On ESP32-P4 we have multiple UARTs. UART0 is the debug/console port.
UART1 or UART2 could be the secondary port.

Implementation: add to t_mos_api:
  int  (*uopen)(uint32_t baud);
  void (*uclose)(void);
  int  (*ugetc)(void);
  int  (*uputc)(uint8_t c);

Wrap ESP-IDF uart driver on UART_NUM_1. Pins TBD (configurable via sdkconfig or hardcoded to P4 header pins).
